How many heartthrobs can you fit in one Hollywood flick?  At least three it seems since Brad Pitt, Christian Bale, and Ryan Gosling are set to star together. Variety reports that Pitt's Plan B production company will tackle another adaptation of a Michael Lewis bestseller following the success of Moneball. The adaptation of 'The Big Short: Inside the Doomsday Machine' will be written and directed by Moneyball helmer Adam McKay and Christian Bale and Ryan Gosling have reportedly signed up to star alongisde Pitt. The book tells the story of the housing and credit bubble that led to the financial crisis that kicked off in 2007. Pitt is fresh from his 12 Years a Slave success whilst Bale's most recent project was Ridley Scott's Exodus: Gods and Kings and Gosling has just finished filming 70s conspiracy thriller The Nice Guys. Online Editors 
